  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 10.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Ezra the priest stood up",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Now that the time had come for action, Ezra was not wanting to his duties. The chief authority had been put into his hands by the Persian king (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 7:25, 26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and he was bound to exercise it. Accordingly, the great bulk of the nation being assembled in obedience to the proclamation, Ezra came forward in person, and declared that the \"strange wives\" must be put away. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Ye have taken strange wives",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Literally, \"have caused to dwell,\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " have made them come and live with you in the holy land. Ezra 10:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ezra then stood up and reproved the assembled multitude, saying: You have brought home (הושׁיב, comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 10:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") strange wives to increase the trespass of Israel (comp. Ezra's confession, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 9:6-15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and exhorted them to give glory to God and to do His pleasure, (viz.) to separate themselves from the people of the land, and from the strange wives. On תודה תּנוּ, comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 7:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Separation from the people of the land consisted, under the circumstances, in the dismissal of the strange wives. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
